{"lemma":"طَيْلَسانَيْ","slug":"طَيْلَسانَيْ","root":"NTWS","root_slug":"NTWS","root_link":"/words/roots/NTWS","pos":"N","pos_camel":"noun","paradigm":[],"frequency_in_corpus":0,"cross_references":{"qac":{"found":false},"wiktextract":{"found":true,"entry_count":1,"pos_tags":["noun"],"has_etymology":true,"sense_count":1},"lanes":{"found":true,"entry_ids":["n26933"],"search_url":"https://lanelexicon.com/?s=%D8%B7%D9%8E%D9%8A%D9%92%D9%84%D9%8E%D8%B3%D8%A7%D9%86%D9%8E%D9%8A%D9%92"}},"translations":null,"definition":{"source":"wiktextract","senses":[{"pos":"noun","gloss":"a rectangular coverlet worn over the shoulders, corresponding to the tallit of the Jews and the pallium of the Romans"}]},"etymology":{"source":"wiktextract","text":"Already in Medieval times understood as an early borrowing of Persian تالشان (tâlešân, “robe”) believed to derive from the region or people name تالش (tâleš, “Talysh”) which itself appears as طَيْلَسَان (ṭaylasān) and الطَيْلَسَان (aṭ-ṭaylasān)."},"ipa":["/tˤaj.la.saːn/","/tˤaj.li.saːn/"],"lanes_definition":{"source":"lanes","entries":[{"entry_id":"n26933","headword_ar":"طَيْلَسَانٌ","root":"Tls","body":[{"kind":"text","text":"(El-Fárábee, S, M, Mgh, O, Msb, K) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"TayolisaAnN","text_ar":"طَيْلِسَانٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (M, O, K,) the latter form used by some, (El-Fárábee, Msb,) or by the vulgar, (S,) and disallowed by As, (M, Msb,) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"TayolusaAnN","text_ar":"طَيْلُسَانٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", all these three forms being mentioned by 'Iyád and others, (K,) [accord. to the TA, following Lth; but the words of Lth, as cited in the TA, and in the O, rather signify that, if, instead of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"TayolisaAnN","text_ar":"طَيْلِسَانٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", with kesr to the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"l","text_ar":"ل"},{"kind":"text","text":", one said"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"TayolusaAnN","text_ar":"طَيْلُسَانٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", with damm to the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"l","text_ar":"ل"},{"kind":"text","text":", like"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"xayozuraAnN","text_ar":"خَيْزُرَانٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"HayosumaAnN","text_ar":"حَيْسُمَانٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", it would be more agreeable with analogy; and the like is said in the Msb, as on the authority of Az;] and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"TayolasN","text_ar":"طَيْلَسٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"(M, Mgh, O, K) and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"TaAlasaAnN","text_ar":"طَالَسَانٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"; (M, TA;) arabicized words, (S, Mgh, Msb, K,) from the Pers., (S, Msb,) originally"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"taAlasaAno","text_ar":"تَالَسَانْ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (as in some copies of the K,) or"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"taAla$aAno","text_ar":"تَالَشَانْ"},{"kind":"text","text":"; (as in other copies of the K, and in some copies of the T, and thus written by El-Urmawee, as is said in the TA, and thus written also in the Mgh;) differently expl. by different persons; (TA;) [app. accord. to the fashions of different times and countries;] accord. to some, (TA,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A certain kind of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"kisaA='","text_ar":"كِسَا=ء"},{"kind":"text","text":": (M, TA:) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a certain article of apparel worn by the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Eajam","text_ar":"عَجَم"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Persians"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"other foreigners"},{"kind":"text","text":"], (Mgh, Msb,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"of a round form, and black;"},{"kind":"text","text":"accord. to the “ Jema et-Tefáreek, ”"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"having its woof and warp both of wool:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Mgh:) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"kisaA='","text_ar":"كِسَا=ء"},{"kind":"text","text":","},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"of a dark,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"an ashy, dust-colour,"},{"kind":"text","text":"("},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^axoDar","text_ar":"اَخْضَر"},{"kind":"text","text":",)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"worn by persons of distinction:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(EshShereeshee, in Har, p. 238:) [see also"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"bat~N","text_ar":"بَتٌّ"},{"kind":"text","text":", and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"saAjN","text_ar":"سَاجٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":": El-Makreezee mentions a kind of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"TylsAn","text_ar":"طيلسان"},{"kind":"page_break","n":1867},{"kind":"text","text":"having a round piece cut out from the middle of it ("},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"muqaw~arN","text_ar":"مُقَوَّرٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":") worn by the Egyptian Wezeer, and called, in his time, (the 14th and 15th centuries of our era,)"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"TaroHapN","text_ar":"طَرْحَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":": (see this word: and see De Sacy's Chrest. Arabe, sec. ed., ii. 267—269; and Dozy's Dict. des Noms des Vêtements chez les Arabes, 278—90:) it seems to have resembled our academic hood, of which it was perhaps the original: the term"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"TylsAn","text_ar":"طيلسان"},{"kind":"text","text":"is now commonly applied to"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"an oblong piece of drapery,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a scarf,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"an oblong shawl, worn in such a manner that one end hangs down upon the side of the bosom, the middle part being turned over the head and under the chin, and the other end being thrown over the shoulder, and hanging down upon the back:"},{"kind":"text","text":"this is worn by many of the professional learned men in winter, in Arabian countries: it is also used in the sense of the word"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Ea*abapN","text_ar":"عَذَبَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", meaning"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"an end of a turban, when made to hang down between the shoulders:"},{"kind":"text","text":"see"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Ea*abN","text_ar":"عَذَبٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":":] the pl. (of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"TayolasaAnN","text_ar":"طَيْلَسَانٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"TayolisaAnN","text_ar":"طَيْلِسَانٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"TayolasN","text_ar":"طَيْلَسٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", M) is"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"TayaAlisapN","text_ar":"طَيَالِسَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (S, M, A, Mgh, Msb, K,) in which the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"p","text_ar":"ة"},{"kind":"text","text":"is added because it is a foreign word, (S, M, K,) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"TayaAlisu","text_ar":"طَيَالِسُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"; (M, A;) or the latter is pl. of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"TayolasN","text_ar":"طَيْلَسٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":": (TA:) I do not know (says ISd) any pl. of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"TaAlasaAnN","text_ar":"طَالَسَانٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":": (M, TA:) it is not allowable to form an abbreviation of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"TayolisaAnN","text_ar":"طَيْلِسَانٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", with kesr to the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"l","text_ar":"ل"},{"kind":"text","text":", as a compellation, because there is no instance of the measure"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"fayoEilN","text_ar":"فَيْعِلٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", with kesr to the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"E","text_ar":"ع"},{"kind":"text","text":", except in infirm words such as"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"say~idN","text_ar":"سَيِّدٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"may~itN","text_ar":"مَيِّتٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":". (S.) Hence the expression, (Mgh,)"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"yaA A@bona","text_ar":"يَا ا@بْنَ"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AlT~ayolasaAni","text_ar":"الطَّيْلَسَانِ"},{"kind":"text","text":", [lit.,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"O son of the teylesán,"},{"kind":"text","text":"] meaning,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"O 'Ajamee,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(A, Mgh,) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Aajamee,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(K,) [i. e.,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Persian,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"foreigner,"},{"kind":"text","text":"] used in reviling another; (Mgh, K;) for the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Eajam","text_ar":"عَجَم"},{"kind":"text","text":"are those who [most commonly] attire themselves with the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"TylsAn","text_ar":"طيلسان"},{"kind":"text","text":". (TA.)       -A2-  See also"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"TalosN","text_ar":"طَلْسٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"."}],"source_refs":["M","O","K","S","Msb","Mgh","TA","A"]}]}}